                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue Trinitatis. <persName ref="#people/261"
                            >Conradus</persName>, divina favente clemencia, Romanorum
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Omnium sancte Dei Ecclesie fidelium et
                        nostrorum, presentibus scilicet ac futurorum universitas noverit, quod
                        <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1992">Ylarius</persName>, <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> <rs key="#Monasteries">coenobii</rs> <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Landed_possessions #Mountains #Wine #Rivers #Riverbed #Castle #Animals #Hay/fodder #Slave #Slave_labour" ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Christi Martyris Vincencii</orgName>, siti
                        in <rs key="#Fines">territorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines #Monasteries #Abbots #Rivers" ref="#estates/1902">Beneventano</geogName>, super <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturnum</placeName>, nostram adiens
                        celsitudinem, detulit precepta precessorum nostrorum imperatorum, et regum
                        [...], per que contulerunt ex suis rebus in prefatum monasterium, ac
                        confirmaverunt res, et possessiones ibi a principibus, ducibus, reliquisque
                        fidelibus collatas. Unde prefatus abbas nos exoravit, ut eadem precepta, ac
                        legales scripciones, nec non predia per diversas fines regni Italici
                        coniacencia eidem cenobio collata, per nostre confirmacionis preceptum, in
                        prefatum locum concederemus, et confirmaremus. Cuius peticionibus faventes,
                        ob interventum <persName key="#Queen #Intercessory" ref="#people/262"
                            >Gisle</persName> <rs key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> nostre dilecte contectalis, ac regis
                        <persName key="#Intercessory" ref="#people/237"
                            >Henrici</persName> nostri amantissimi filii, per hanc <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">preceptalem confirmacionem</rs>,
                        prout iuste et legaliter possumus, concedimus, et confirmamus, ac penitus
                        corroboramus in predicto monasterio omnia <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">precepta</rs> precessorum nostrorum
                        imperatorum et <rs key="#Emperor/king">regum</rs>, videlicet 
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/249"
                            >Desiderii</persName>, 
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/14"
                            >Karoli</persName>, <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/118"
                                >Lodoici</persName>, atque <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                                    ref="#people/9">Lotharii</persName>
                        atque imperatoris <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/130">Henrici</persName>, verumtamen omnes res, et possessiones per
                        diversos fines regni Italici positas, per eadem precepta, vel quolibet
                        legales scripciones a principibus, ducibus reliquisque fidelibus ibidem
                        collatas, nec non monasteria et cellas inferius nominatas, primitus
                        videlicet declarantes ipsas hereditates, que circumdant ipsum monasterium,
                        per has quoque fines: incipientes itaque a <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2323">Sangro</placeName>,
                        deinde per <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#places/2814">montes publicos</placeName> usque in <rs
                                key="#Mountains">montem</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName
                                    key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    ref="#places/2324">Acze</placeName>, et sic
                        revolventes montes eodem usque in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/2327">Melfa</placeName>, et quemadmodum
                        decurrit ipsa Melfa, usque ubi coniungit se cum <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2813">Mellarino</placeName>, et abhinc in
                        verticem <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montis</rs>, qui dicitur Barbola, et sic per cilium montis eiusdem,
                        usque in montem Archanum, et montem Marthe, montemque <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2325">Casale</placeName>; eosque
                        videlicet montes extrinsecus circumdantes in hortum <rs key="#Rivers">riaginis</rs>
                        , <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2309">Ravennola</placeName> qui
                        nominatur; et a capite eiusdem riaginis venientes iuxta <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention">montes puplicos</rs>,
                        usque in montem <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2326">Benafranum</placeName>, qui est super <placeName
                                key="#Cities" ref="#places/2300">urbem</placeName>; eodem vero revolvente monte
                        usque in cilium montis, qui est super <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs>, que vocatur <geogName
                                key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/1929">Arcora</geogName>, que est
                        <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesie</rs> hereditas <orgName
                                key="#Landed_possessions #Churches #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/1904">Sancte Dei genitricis Marie</orgName>, que vocatur <placeName
                                    key="#Churches #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    ref="#places/2330">Olivetum</placeName>,
                        subiecta prefato monasterio, et ecclesie nichilominus hereditas <orgName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1910">Sancte
                            Cristine</orgName>, subdita eidem cenobio cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions">territoriis</rs> suis, et cum reliquis
                        finibus, ipsa hereditas circumdata usque in <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs> <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturnum</placeName>; nam iterum ex
                        alia parte inchoantes a primo fine cum iam dicto fluvio Sangro, ipsosque
                        relinquentes, quomodo decernit aparu colle, et pergens usque in <rs
                            key="#Rivers">rivum</rs> qui
                        dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/2328">Foruli</placeName>, eodemque decurrente rivo, 
                        usque in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs> <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2329">Vantra</placeName>, et
                        quomodo decurrit ipsum flumen in alio flumine quod Vulturnus vocatur, et
                        quemadmodum ipsum decurrit flumen, iuxta terras eiusdem monasterii, usque in
                        predictos fines, et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs> ecclesie Sancte Marie. 
                        Per has quoque fines una
                        cum <rs key="#Slave #Slave_labour">servis</rs> et ancillis cespitibusque suis, 
                        necnon et <rs key="#Castle">castris</rs>, montibus,
                        collibus, vallibus, ecclesiis, <rs key="#Rivers #Riverbed"
                            >aaquis</rs>, <rs key="#Animals #Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>, et omnia infra ipsos fines
                        manencia, per nostram presentem autoritatem prefato monasterio concedimus,
                        et confirmamus. Insuper corroboramus in eodem monasterio: <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterium</rs> <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1967">Petri
                            apostoli</orgName>, positum in loco <placeName key="#Monasteries"
                                ref="#places/2357">Trite</placeName>; et in <placeName
                                    key="#Cells/hermitages #Slave #Slave_labour #Landed_possessions #Rivers"
                                    ref="#places/1820">Penne</placeName> <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs> unam, 
                        que dicitur <orgName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Slave #Slave_labour #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1974">Sancta
                            Maria in Musano</orgName>; in Abruczo <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs> unam in 
                        loco, qui dicitur <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2806">Arole</placeName>; item
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1956">Sancta Maria in Duas Basilicas</orgName>
                        : seu et <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1940">Sancte Marie</orgName> in
                        territorio Marsicano, in loco Apinianici; item in <rs key="#City_territory">finibus</rs> <placeName key="#Cities City_territory #Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2001">
                            Sorane</placeName> <rs key="#Cities">civitatis</rs>
                        inclitam <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2819">vallem Soranam</placeName>
                        , cum omnibus <rs key="#Landed_possessions">pertinenciis</rs> et terris in ipsis
                        partibus consistentibus, subditas eidem monasterio, per cognitas fines,
                        sicut precepta eiusdem continent cenobii, et scripciones ibidem a bonis
